                <aside class="aside aside1">
                    <h2 id="index1">
                        The Quiet American Gardener  
                    </h2>
                    <div class="video-responsive"><!-- Video trailer -->
                        <iframe src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/218796214" width="640" height="360" frameborder="0" webkitallowfullscreen mozallowfullscreen allowfullscreen></iframe>
                    </div>
                    <p>
                        <br>Lawrence Johnston had an artist’s eye, an architect’s sense of space, and a consuming passion for plants. But while the individual rooms within the gardens he created made a satisfying whole, for the visitor, when viewed holistically, they can be a bewildering and confusing experience.
                        <br>
                        <br>This two-part documentary series on Major Lawrence Johnston, the creator of Hidcote Manor Garden in Gloucestershire, England and Jardin Serre de la Madone in France, takes us through each garden as Lawrence Johnston had originally developed it, highlighting the arrangements of space which were filled with beautiful plants and foliage.
                    </p>
                    <span class="text-muted">
                        <h4>
                            Available on DVD from the National Trust
                        </h4>
                    </span>
                </aside>

