                <aside class="aside aside2">
                    <aside class="aside aside1">
                        <h2 id="index3">
                            A Glimpse of Greenland: The Disappearing Ice  
                        </h2>
                        <div class="video-responsive"><!-- Video trailer -->
                            <iframe src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/218799891" width="640" height="360" frameborder="0" webkitallowfullscreen mozallowfullscreen allowfullscreen></iframe>
                        </div>
                        <p>
                            <br>GLIMPSE is a 5-year glaciology research project based at the Department of Geography, Swansea University in South Wales (U.K.). Through the use of international collaborative research, fieldwork, remote sensing and modelling techniques, its objectives are to gain an understanding of how Greenland’s melting ice sheet is impacting on the Earth. Dr Lawrence Dyke presents the project&rsquo;s findings.
                        </p>

