            <div class="flex-container">
                <aside class="aside aside3">
                    <h2 id="index4">
                        Neptune&rsquo;s Future  
                    </h2>
                    <div class="video-responsive"><!-- Video trailer -->
                        <iframe src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/215995250" width="640" height="352" frameborder="0" webkitallowfullscreen mozallowfullscreen allowfullscreen></iframe>
                    </div>
                    <h4>National Trust: Neptune Coastline Campaign.<br>Caring for Britain&rsquo;s coastline for future generations.</h4>
                    <p>
                        <br>With more than 700 miles of Britain’s shoreline coming under the care of the National Trust, this 60 minute documentary, Neptune&rsquo;s Future, with Kate Humble, was commissioned by the Trust as part of its national Neptune Coastline Campaign. The aims and objectives of the campaign were: 
                    </p>
                    <ul class='neptune-left'><li>
                            To celebrate the beauty and diversity of Britain&rsquo;s coastline heritage.    
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            To raise awareness of the challenges global warming and the resulting rise in sea levels will bring, through an understanding of the past and a celebration of the present.        
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            To inform the public of the National Trust&rsquo;s strategic planning for the future and;      
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            To raise funds for the National Trust&rsquo;s continuing commitment to Britain’s coastline.     
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                    <span class="text-muted">
                        <h4>
                            Available on DVD from the National Trust
                        </h4>
                    </span>
                </aside>

