                <aside class="aside aside4">
                    <h2 id="index6">
                        The search for Solomon  
                    </h2>
                    <div class="video-responsive"><!-- Video trailer -->
                        <iframe src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/268262560" width="640" height="360" frameborder="0" webkitallowfullscreen mozallowfullscreen allowfullscreen></iframe>
                    </div>
                    <h4>
                        The Water Gate and Projecting Tower of the Solomonic wall at the Ophel, Jerusalem.  
                    </h4>
                    <p>
                        <br>Archaeologists from The Hebrew University of Jerusalem have revealed an ancient path they believe to date back to the time of King Solomon, along with other structures which include a gateway and the foundations to a building.<br>
                        <br>“This is the first time a building has been found that matches descriptions of the building carried out by King Solomon in Jerusalem.” - <a href="http://www.israelnationalnews.com/News/News.aspx/136130"> Dr Eilat Mazar.</a><br>
                        <br>But do these findings come from the time of King Solomon or a later period?
                    </p>
